12/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- UK Foreign Office Political Director John Sawers met with Serbian President Boris Tadic and the head of the Co-ordination Centre for Kosovo and Metohija, Nebojsa Covic on Friday (10 December). 
They focused on issues involving Kosovo and Metohija. 
Both Tadic and Covic criticised the appointment of Ramush Haradinaj as Kosovo prime minister. 
Covic said the appointment dealt a serious blow to the process of building a multi-ethnic society in the province. 
Tadic urged the international community to address the controversy surrounding Haradinaj. 
He also recommended that Belgrade continue dialogue with Kosovo institutions, to defend the rights of its citizens. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 10/12/04)
